    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Cut your <strong>apple[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into wedges and discard the core</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>carrot discs</strong>, <strong>onion wedges and apple</strong> <strong>wedges </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>grated garlic</strong> with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl \u2013 these are your <strong>garlic breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 20 min, remove the dish from the oven and top the vegetables with the <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>garlic breadcrumbs</strong> then return the dish to the oven and cook for a further 20-25 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the breadcrumbs are golden</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Combine <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chives </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)<strong> </strong>with your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[125ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chive & mustard sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is cooked through, remove the dish from the oven and pour in the <strong>chive & mustard sauce</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven and cook for a further 2-3 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic crusted pork loin bake with chive & mustard sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-crusted-pork-loin-bake-with-chive-and-mustard-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlic crusted pork loin steak </strong>with the <strong>roasted vegetables </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>chives & mustard sauce</strong> and garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped chives</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
